# Google Ads API
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# How to get these:
#
#   1. Developer token
#      https://ads.google.com → Tools & Settings → Setup → API Center
#      Apply for access. "Test" tokens work only against test accounts;
#      "Standard" is needed for production. Approval can take days.
#
#   2. OAuth client (client_id + client_secret)
#      Google Cloud Console → APIs & Services → Credentials
#         → Create Credentials → OAuth client ID → Desktop app
#      Enable "Google Ads API" on the same GCP project.
#
#   3. Refresh token
#      Run the official helper once on a machine with a browser:
#         pip install google-ads
#         python -m google.ads.googleads.examples.authentication.generate_user_credentials \
#             --client_id $CLIENT_ID --client_secret $CLIENT_SECRET
#      Approve in browser, copy the printed refresh_token here.
#
#   4. Login customer ID (MCC only)
#      The MCC (manager) account ID, no dashes. Skip if you only have
#      a single non-MCC customer.

GOOGLE_ADS_DEVELOPER_TOKEN=
GOOGLE_ADS_CLIENT_ID=
GOOGLE_ADS_CLIENT_SECRET=
GOOGLE_ADS_REFRESH_TOKEN=
GOOGLE_ADS_LOGIN_CUSTOMER_ID=     # e.g. 1234567890 (MCC). Leave blank if not MCC.
